# {{SITE_TITLE}}

A static site generated from a gm-apprentice campaign vault.

## Getting started

1. Install dependencies:
   ```
   npm install
   ```

2. Edit `vault.config.json` to point `vaultPath` at your Obsidian vault.

3. Build the site:
   ```
   npm run build
   ```

The generated site will be written to the `outputDir` specified in `vault.config.json`.

## Deployment

Push the contents of your output directory to GitHub Pages or any static host.
The included `.nojekyll` file ensures GitHub Pages serves the site without Jekyll processing.
